## Work Environment

### Datascience Workspace (`~/workspace/git/datascience/`)

Multi-repo workspace (6 independent git repos, not a monorepo). See the group-level `CLAUDE.md` in that directory for repo details, cross-repo workflows, and deployment pipeline docs.

### AWS & Kubernetes
- **NEVER patch live Kubernetes resources directly** (`kubectl apply/patch/edit`) without explicit user permission. Make code/Terraform changes → show plan → wait for user to apply. Direct kubectl changes bypass Terraform state and cause `resourceVersion` conflicts requiring `terraform state rm` to recover.
- SSO: `aws sso login --sso-session KN-Operations`
- Profiles: `dev`, `prod`
- Update kubectl binary to match cluster version: `update_kubectl` (does NOT update kubeconfig contexts)
- Check available contexts: `kubectl config get-contexts` — context names are full ARNs (e.g. `arn:aws:eks:eu-central-1:...:cluster/apps-prod-cluster`)
- Pod log retention is very short (minutes to ~1 hour due to kubelet rotation) — for historical logs, query Loki instead
- **ALWAYS verify kubectl context before any kubectl command**: run `kubectl config current-context` first
- **Pass `--context=<name>` directly** to each command — never rely on ambient context being set correctly
- **Confirm target cluster** (sandbox/dev/prod) with user before any mutating operation

### Observability (Grafana/Loki)
- **Architecture**: Grafana Alloy collectors (in `monitoring` ns) → centralized Loki → centralized Grafana
- **Grafana (dev)**: `grafana.nonprod.example.com` — `apps-dev-cluster`
- **Grafana (prod)**: `grafana.prod.example.com` — `apps-prod-cluster`
- **Querying logs via CLI**: Use Grafana session cookie (no K8s access needed). `export GRAFANA_SESSION_DEV=<cookie>` / `GRAFANA_SESSION_PROD=<cookie>`. Get cookie: browser DevTools → Application → Cookies → `grafana_session`. Query via `/api/datasources/proxy/<id>/loki/api/v1/query_range` (POST with `--data-urlencode`). Default datascience datasource: `aie-grafana-loki` (id 221 on dev).
- **Direct Loki auth**: OAuth2 client credentials from `monitoring/alloy-oauth2-credentials` K8s secret. Token endpoint is AWS Cognito — only `client_credentials` grant supported, no personal user CLI auth.
- **Tenant/cluster mapping**: Check the Alloy configmap in `monitoring` ns for `tenant_id` and `external_labels`

### Jira
- `jira` CLI on PATH — prefer over REST API. Auth: `export JIRA_API_TOKEN=$(bw_get_secret "Jira API Token")`
- **Default project:** `AI` (AI and Data Science) — **always add label `AIE`** on tickets
- **Always ask** which epic to attach the ticket to (if applicable)
- **Formatting gotcha:** `jira issue create -b`/`-T` mangles Jira wiki markup (escapes special chars, converts `#` lists to `h1.`). Workaround: create ticket with CLI, then update description via REST API: `curl -X PUT -H "Authorization: Bearer $JIRA_API_TOKEN" -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d @body.json "https://jira.example.com/rest/api/2/issue/{KEY}"`
- **Always invoke the `working-with-jira` skill** before doing any Jira operations
- Full CLI/REST reference in `working-with-jira` skill (kn-internal-tools plugin)

### Confluence (wiki.example.com)
- REST API + `mark` CLI. Auth: `bw_get_secret "Confluence API Token"` (separate from Jira PAT) — `mark` reads it via `MARK_PASSWORD` env var; NOT in chezmoi (no passwords in git), set manually each session
- Full reference in `working-with-confluence` skill (kn-internal-tools plugin)

### Chezmoi (Dotfiles)
- Home dir files managed by chezmoi. **Never edit template targets directly** (`~/CLAUDE.md`, `~/.claude/settings.json`)
- Full workflow in `editing-dotfiles-with-chezmoi` skill (`~/.claude/skills/`)
- `chezmoi forget` needs `--force` in non-interactive shells (no TTY for confirmation)
- Autocommit only fires on `chezmoi add`/`re-add` — direct source edits need manual `git -C ~/.local/share/chezmoi` commit
- **Go template whitespace**: `{{ "{{" }}- if }}` (left-dash) trims before — preserves indentation of next line. `{{ "{{" }} if -}}` (right-dash) trims after — use for block-level conditionals. Inline for single values: `{{ "{{" }} if .x }}val1{{ "{{" }} else }}val2{{ "{{" }} end }}`

